Sentiment

Winston Saunders

May 9, 2016

SUMMARY

This continuation of BIAS AND CONTEXT IN PRESIDENTIAL DEBATE TEXTS and HEAT MAPS & LINGUISTICS OF DEBATE SPEECH in R, which focused on a “Bag of Words” approach to analyzing the text of Presidential Debates for the 2016 Election Cycle.

This extends the analysis to include “sentiment” analysis based on standard semiment models using the {virdis} package in R.

DATA SOURCES AND METHODS

The text of the presidential debates are downloaded from the UCSB Presidency Project. Transcripts were pasted into Apple Pages and stored as unformatted .txt files.

Compute Sentiment

We’ll use mutate to add a “Sentiment” column to the data.

## add sentiment using two different methods
d_all_f <- mutate(d_all_f, afinn_sentiment = get_sentiment(d_all_f$text, method = "afinn"), bing_sentiment = get_sentiment(d_all_f$text, method = "bing"))
r_all_f <- mutate(r_all_f, afinn_sentiment = get_sentiment(r_all_f$text, method = "afinn"), bing_sentiment = get_sentiment(r_all_f$text, method = "bing"))
